.TH THOP 1 "January 2026" "thop 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
thop \- Terminal Hopper for Agents
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B thop
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B thop
is a CLI tool that enables AI agents to execute commands on remote systems
via SSH. It provides a shell wrapper architecture with session management,
automatic reconnection, and context persistence.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-proxy
Run in proxy mode (for AI agents). Reads commands from stdin and outputs
results to stdout.
.TP
.B \-c \fICOMMAND\fR
Execute a single command and exit with its exit code.
.TP
.B \-\-status
Show all sessions and their status, then exit.
.TP
.B \-\-config \fIPATH\fR
Use alternate config file (default: ~/.config/thop/config.toml).
.TP
.B \-\-json
Output in JSON format.
.TP
.B \-\-completions \fISHELL\fR
Generate shell completions (bash, zsh, fish).
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-verbose
Increase logging verbosity.
.TP
.B \-q, \-\-quiet
Suppress non-error output.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Print help information.
.TP
.B \-V, \-\-version
Print version information.
.SH INTERACTIVE COMMANDS
.TP
.B /connect \fISESSION\fR
Establish SSH connection to a session.
.TP
.B /switch \fISESSION\fR
Change active context to a session.
.TP
.B /local
Switch to local shell (alias for /switch local).
.TP
.B /status
Show all sessions and their status.
.TP
.B /close \fISESSION\fR
Close SSH connection to a session.
.TP
.B /env [\fIKEY=VALUE\fR]
Show or set environment variables.
.TP
.B /help
Show available commands.
.SH EXIT CODES
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error
.TP
.B 2
Authentication failed
.TP
.B 3
Host key verification failed
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/thop/config.toml
User configuration file.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/thop/state.json
Session state file.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/thop/thop.log
Log file.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B THOP_CONFIG
Path to config file.
.TP
.B THOP_STATE_FILE
Path to state file.
.TP
.B THOP_LOG_LEVEL
Log level (debug, info, warn, error).
.TP
.B THOP_DEFAULT_SESSION
Default session name.
